(27, 'Это пост-проверка добавления , как через редактор.', '-', 'Это пост-проверка добавления , как через редактор.', '<div class=\"css-s99gbd StoryBodyCompanionColumn\" data-testid=\"companionColumn-1\">\r\n<div class=\"css-53u6y8\">\r\n<p class=\"css-at9mc1 evys1bk0\">&ldquo;Everyone in Scotland hates him,&rdquo; Mr. Forbes said, a claim that was thrown in doubt a few minutes later by John Duncan, a nearby contractor who clears ditches for Mr. Trump. &ldquo;I love the man,&rdquo; Mr. Duncan said, noting that the president&rsquo;s resort, Trump International Scotland, employs 35 greenskeepers alone.</p>\r\n</div>\r\n<aside class=\"css-ew4tgv\" aria-label=\"companion column\"></aside>\r\n</div>\r\n<div data-testid=\"ImageBlock-3\">\r\n<div data-testid=\"imageblock-wrapper\">\r\n<figure class=\"img-sz-large css-hxpw2c e1g7ppur0\" role=\"group\" aria-label=\"media\">\r\n<div class=\"css-1xdhyk6 erfvjey0\" data-testid=\"photoviewer-children-figure\"><span class=\"css-1ly73wi e1tej78p0\">Image</span><picture><source srcset=\"https://static01.nyt.com/images/2025/07/23/multimedia/23int-trump-scotland-dispatch-2-kzth/23int-trump-scotland-dispatch-2-kzth-mobileMasterAt3x.jpg?quality=75&amp;auto=webp&amp;disable=upscale&amp;width=1800\" media=\"(max-width: 599px) and (min-device-pixel-ratio: 3),(max-width: 599px) and (min-resolution: 3dppx),(max-width: 599px) and (min-resolution: 288dpi)\"><source srcset=\"https://static01.nyt.com/images/2025/07/23/multimedia/23int-trump-scotland-dispatch-2-kzth/23int-trump-scotland-dispatch-2-kzth-mobileMasterAt3x.jpg?quality=75&amp;auto=webp&amp;disable=upscale&amp;width=1200\" media=\"(max-width: 599px) and (min-device-pixel-ratio: 2),(max-width: 599px) and (min-resolution: 2dppx),(max-width: 599px) and (min-resolution: 192dpi)\"><source srcset=\"https://static01.nyt.com/images/2025/07/23/multimedia/23int-trump-scotland-dispatch-2-kzth/23int-trump-scotland-dispatch-2-kzth-mobileMasterAt3x.jpg?quality=75&amp;auto=webp&amp;disable=upscale&amp;width=600\" media=\"(max-width: 599px) and (min-device-pixel-ratio: 1),(max-width: 599px) and (min-resolution: 1dppx),(max-width: 599px) and (min-resolution: 96dpi)\"><img class=\"css-r3fift\" src=\"https://static01.nyt.com/images/2025/07/23/multimedia/23int-trump-scotland-dispatch-2-kzth/23int-trump-scotland-dispatch-2-kzth-articleLarge.jpg?quality=75&amp;auto=webp&amp;disable=upscale\" sizes=\"((min-width: 600px) and (max-width: 1004px)) 84vw, (min-width: 1005px) 80vw, 100vw\" srcset=\"https://static01.nyt.com/images/2025/07/23/multimedia/23int-trump-scotland-dispatch-2-kzth/23int-trump-scotland-dispatch-2-kzth-articleLarge.jpg?quality=75&amp;auto=webp 600w,https://static01.nyt.com/images/2025/07/23/multimedia/23int-trump-scotland-dispatch-2-kzth/23int-trump-scotland-dispatch-2-kzth-jumbo.jpg?quality=75&amp;auto=webp 1024w,https://static01.nyt.com/images/2025/07/23/multimedia/23int-trump-scotland-dispatch-2-kzth/23int-trump-scotland-dispatch-2-kzth-superJumbo.jpg?quality=75&amp;auto=webp 2048w\" alt=\"A mustached man in a blue t-shirt stands with his hands in his pockets in a doorway lined with rose bushes.\" width=\"600\" height=\"400\"></picture></div>\r\n<figcaption class=\"css-1g9ic6e ewdxa0s0\" data-testid=\"photoviewer-children-caption\"><span class=\"css-jevhma e13ogyst0\">&ldquo;There&rsquo;s no way I&rsquo;m ever going to sell,&rdquo; said Michael Forbes, whose property is surrounded by Mr. Trump&rsquo;s new golf course.</span></figcaption>\r\n</figure>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div data-testid=\"ImageBlock-4\">\r\n<div data-testid=\"imageblock-wrapper\">\r\n<figure class=\"img-sz-large css-hxpw2c e1g7ppur0\" role=\"group\" aria-label=\"media\">\r\n<div class=\"css-1xdhyk6 erfvjey0\" data-testid=\"photoviewer-children-figure\"><span class=\"css-1ly73wi e1tej78p0\">Image</span>\r\n<div class=\"css-1pq3dr9\" data-testid=\"lazy-image\">\r\n<div data-testid=\"lazyimage-container\"><picture class=\"css-1j5kxti\"><source srcset=\"https://static01.nyt.com/images/2025/07/23/multimedia/23int-trump-scotland-scene-3-fvlc/23int-trump-scotland-scene-3-fvlc-mobileMasterAt3x.jpg?quality=75&amp;auto=webp&amp;disable=upscale&amp;width=1800\" media=\"(max-width: 599px) and (min-device-pixel-ratio: 3),(max-width: 599px) and (min-resolution: 3dppx),(max-width: 599px) and (min-resolution: 288dpi)\"><source srcset=\"https://static01.nyt.com/images/2025/07/23/multimedia/23int-trump-scotland-scene-3-fvlc/23int-trump-scotland-scene-3-fvlc-mobileMasterAt3x.jpg?quality=75&amp;auto=webp&amp;disable=upscale&amp;width=1200\" media=\"(max-width: 599px) and (min-device-pixel-ratio: 2),(max-width: 599px) and (min-resolution: 2dppx),(max-width: 599px) and (min-resolution: 192dpi)\"><source srcset=\"https://static01.nyt.com/images/2025/07/23/multimedia/23int-trump-scotland-scene-3-fvlc/23int-trump-scotland-scene-3-fvlc-mobileMasterAt3x.jpg?quality=75&amp;auto=webp&amp;disable=upscale&amp;width=600\" media=\"(max-width: 599px) and (min-device-pixel-ratio: 1),(max-width: 599px) and (min-resolution: 1dppx),(max-width: 599px) and (min-resolution: 96dpi)\"><img class=\"css-1m50asq\" src=\"https://static01.nyt.com/images/2025/07/23/multimedia/23int-trump-scotland-scene-3-fvlc/23int-trump-scotland-scene-3-fvlc-articleLarge.jpg?quality=75&amp;auto=webp&amp;disable=upscale\" sizes=\"((min-width: 600px) and (max-width: 1004px)) 84vw, (min-width: 1005px) 80vw, 100vw\" srcset=\"https://static01.nyt.com/images/2025/07/23/multimedia/23int-trump-scotland-scene-3-fvlc/23int-trump-scotland-scene-3-fvlc-articleLarge.jpg?quality=75&amp;auto=webp 600w,https://static01.nyt.com/images/2025/07/23/multimedia/23int-trump-scotland-scene-3-fvlc/23int-trump-scotland-scene-3-fvlc-jumbo.jpg?quality=75&amp;auto=webp 1024w,https://static01.nyt.com/images/2025/07/23/multimedia/23int-trump-scotland-scene-3-fvlc/23int-trump-scotland-scene-3-fvlc-superJumbo.jpg?quality=75&amp;auto=webp 2048w\" alt=\"A barn painted with the words &ldquo;No More Trump Lies&rdquo; and a mural of a man in a Scottish beret making a fist.\" loading=\"lazy\"></picture></div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<figcaption class=\"css-1g9ic6e ewdxa0s0\" data-testid=\"photoviewer-children-caption\"><span class=\"css-jevhma e13ogyst0\">Mr. Forbes uses his farm buildings to send his neighbor a message.</span></figcaption>\r\n</figure>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"css-s99gbd StoryBodyCompanionColumn\" data-testid=\"companionColumn-2\">\r\n<div class=\"css-53u6y8\">\r\n<p class=\"css-at9mc1 evys1bk0\">Mr. Duncan likened Mr. Trump to Nigel Farage, the populist leader of the anti-immigrant party Reform U.K., and said Britain would benefit from their brand of take-no-prisoners leadership. Still, he conceded, &ldquo;There&rsquo;s folks who don&rsquo;t like Donald Trump, and nothing is ever going to change that.&rdquo;</p>\r\n<p class=\"css-at9mc1 evys1bk0\">The police in Scotland are bracing for demonstrations against Mr. Trump during his visit, which will include a weekend at his other Scottish resort, Trump Turnberry, on the west coast about 50 miles from Glasgow. A survey in February by the market research firm Ipsos found that 71 percent of those polled in Scotland had an unfavorable opinion of Mr. Trump, compared with 57 percent of the broader British public polled.</p>\r\n<p class=\"css-at9mc1 evys1bk0\">Some of this antipathy may reflect his turbulent history in Scotland, which has been marked by feuds with noncompliant neighbors, breakups with political officials over his business plans, and longstanding grudges, like Mr. Trump&rsquo;s hostility toward the offshore windmills that turn lazily within sight of his guests in Aberdeenshire.</p>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>', '', '/uploads/da6c4e11-1d90-4568-88ae-66d223236dfb_Снимок экрана (706).png', '2025-08-01', '2025-08-01 06:45:00', '2025-08-01 06:45:00'),
(28, 'A French Beach Town’s Plea to Tourists: Keep Your Clothes On', 'a-french-beach-towns-plea-to-tourists-keep-your-clothes-on', 'A French Beach Town’s Plea to Tourists: Keep Your Clothes On', '<header class=\"css-1qv3lay euiyums1\">\r\n<div class=\"css-1vkm6nb ehdk2mb0\">\r\n<h1 id=\"link-9799cdd\" class=\"css-88wicj e1h9rw200\" data-testid=\"headline\">A French Beach Town&rsquo;s Plea to Tourists: Keep Your Clothes On</h1>\r\n</div>\r\n<p id=\"article-summary\" class=\"css-79rysd e1wiw3jv0\">&ldquo;A little restraint, please!&rdquo; wrote the mayor of Les Sables d&rsquo;Olonne, who is leading an effort to stop visitors from wandering the town in just their swimwear.</p>\r\n<div class=\"css-qznc1j\">\r\n<div class=\"css-1e4xg23\">\r\n<div class=\"css-1von7hd\">\r\n<div class=\"css-b8gc4a\">\r\n<div class=\"css-79elbk\">&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div class=\"css-uepebd\">\r\n<div class=\"css-35ezg3\">Listen to this article&nbsp;&middot; 3:12 min&nbsp;<span class=\"css-14h5vr8\"><a href=\"https://help.nytimes.com/hc/en-us/articles/24318293692180\">Learn more</a></span></div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"css-1pec0v7\">\r\n<div class=\"css-yomkvi\" role=\"toolbar\" data-testid=\"share-tools\" aria-label=\"Social Media Share buttons, Save button, and Comments Panel with current comment count\">\r\n<div class=\"css-17cfcd4\">&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div class=\"css-ac2f9k\" data-testid=\"share-tools-menu\">\r\n<ul class=\"css-16g9egj\" data-testid=\"share-tools-list\">\r\n<li class=\"css-1obgmli\">\r\n<div class=\"css-vxcmzt\">\r\n<div class=\"css-79elbk\"><button class=\"css-1eeh360 actionbar-button\" type=\"button\" aria-label=\"\" aria-expanded=\"false\" data-testid=\"gift-article-button\"><span class=\"css-10d8k1f\">Share full article</span></button></div>\r\n</div>\r\n</li>\r\n<li class=\"css-19yhb3c\">\r\n<div class=\"css-vxcmzt\">\r\n<div class=\"css-79elbk\">&nbsp;</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</li>\r\n<li class=\"css-19yhb3c save-button\">&nbsp;</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div data-testid=\"imageblock-wrapper\">\r\n<figure class=\"sizeMedium layoutHorizontal css-nlqgyf\" role=\"group\" aria-label=\"media\">\r\n<div class=\"css-1xb94ky\" data-testid=\"imageContainer-children-Image\"><picture><source srcset=\"https://static01.nyt.com/images/2025/07/30/multimedia/30xp-bikini-apcu/30xp-bikini-apcu-mobileMasterAt3x.jpg?quality=75&amp;auto=webp&amp;disable=upscale&amp;width=1800\" media=\"(max-width: 599px) and (min-device-pixel-ratio: 3),(max-width: 599px) and (min-resolution: 3dppx),(max-width: 599px) and (min-resolution: 288dpi)\"><source srcset=\"https://static01.nyt.com/images/2025/07/30/multimedia/30xp-bikini-apcu/30xp-bikini-apcu-mobileMasterAt3x.jpg?quality=75&amp;auto=webp&amp;disable=upscale&amp;width=1200\" media=\"(max-width: 599px) and (min-device-pixel-ratio: 2),(max-width: 599px) and (min-resolution: 2dppx),(max-width: 599px) and (min-resolution: 192dpi)\"><source srcset=\"https://static01.nyt.com/images/2025/07/30/multimedia/30xp-bikini-apcu/30xp-bikini-apcu-mobileMasterAt3x.jpg?quality=75&amp;auto=webp&amp;disable=upscale&amp;width=600\" media=\"(max-width: 599px) and (min-device-pixel-ratio: 1),(max-width: 599px) and (min-resolution: 1dppx),(max-width: 599px) and (min-resolution: 96dpi)\"><img class=\"css-rq4mmj\" src=\"https://static01.nyt.com/images/2025/07/30/multimedia/30xp-bikini-apcu/30xp-bikini-apcu-articleLarge.jpg?quality=75&amp;auto=webp&amp;disable=upscale\" sizes=\"((min-width: 600px) and (max-width: 1004px)) 84vw, (min-width: 1005px) 60vw, 100vw\" srcset=\"https://static01.nyt.com/images/2025/07/30/multimedia/30xp-bikini-apcu/30xp-bikini-apcu-articleLarge.jpg?quality=75&amp;auto=webp 600w,https://static01.nyt.com/images/2025/07/30/multimedia/30xp-bikini-apcu/30xp-bikini-apcu-jumbo.jpg?quality=75&amp;auto=webp 1024w,https://static01.nyt.com/images/2025/07/30/multimedia/30xp-bikini-apcu/30xp-bikini-apcu-superJumbo.jpg?quality=75&amp;auto=webp 2048w\" alt=\"High-rise buildings are visible in the distance, behind a throng of people with brightly colored umbrellas on a beach.\" width=\"600\" height=\"400\"></picture></div>\r\n<figcaption class=\"css-ktho12 e3rygrp0\" data-testid=\"photoviewer-children-ImageCaption\"><span class=\"css-jevhma e13ogyst0\">La Grande Plage, the beach in Les Sables d&rsquo;Olonne, France, in 2021. The town fines tourists who venture beyond the sand in their swimsuits.</span><span class=\"css-14fe1uy e1z0qqy90\"><span class=\"css-1ly73wi e1tej78p0\">Credit...</span><span aria-hidden=\"false\">Shutterstock</span></span></figcaption>\r\n</figure>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"css-p6m5rf\">\r\n<div class=\"byline-container css-1u5onbp epjyd6m2\">\r\n<div class=\"css-165eim7 ey68jwv0\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><a class=\"css-uwwqev\" href=\"https://www.nytimes.com/by/jenny-gross\"><img class=\"css-dc6zx6 ey68jwv2\" title=\"Jenny Gross\" src=\"https://static01.nyt.com/images/2020/03/06/reader-center/author-jenny-gross/author-jenny-gross-thumbLarge-v5.png\" alt=\"Jenny Gross\"></a></div>\r\n<div class=\"css-233int epjyd6m1\">\r\n<p class=\"css-4anu6l e1jsehar1\"><span class=\"byline-prefix\">By&nbsp;</span><a class=\"last-byline css-ojhyzr e1jsehar0\" itemprop=\"name\" href=\"https://www.nytimes.com/by/jenny-gross\">Jenny Gross</a></p>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"css-1c72mta\"><time class=\"css-kx0gap e16638kd0\" datetime=\"2025-08-01T00:01:05-04:00\">Aug. 1, 2025,&nbsp;<span class=\"css-epvm6\">12:01 a.m. ET</span></time></div>\r\n</header>\r\n<section class=\"meteredContent css-ar1ez3\">\r\n<div class=\"css-s99gbd StoryBodyCompanionColumn\" data-testid=\"companionColumn-0\">\r\n<div class=\"css-53u6y8\">\r\n<p class=\"css-at9mc1 evys1bk0\">A seaside town in France is clamping down on tourists who venture beyond the sand in their swimsuits.</p>\r\n<p class=\"css-at9mc1 evys1bk0\">&ldquo;<a class=\"css-yywogo\" title=\"\" href=\"https://www.facebook.com/YannickMoreau85/posts/pfbid02BqfqqfNdnTb1iHrzj9mB14btAW9ie2tirF4Pkb5Cp3Ct1ZVqF9SaM8yULyx9Q7Ril\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">A little restraint</a>, please!&rdquo; Yannick Moreau, the mayor of Les Sables d&rsquo;Olonne, pleaded on social media last week to the flocks of mostly French tourists who visit each summer.</p>\r\n<p class=\"css-at9mc1 evys1bk0\">Mr. Moreau said in an interview that the behavior had become more prevalent in recent years: Visitors leave the beach and walk into the town&rsquo;s markets, grocery stores and restaurants in their bathing suits. He has seen enough.</p>\r\n<p class=\"css-at9mc1 evys1bk0\">&ldquo;If you go to a market to buy local food &mdash; fruits, vegetables, meat &mdash; you cannot be half-naked with hair falling onto vegetables,&rdquo; he said, adding, &ldquo;It&rsquo;s a matter of decency.&rdquo;</p>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</section>', '', '/uploads/ae360b62-3d68-49d2-b0f5-263e12e09153_G-STRING-THONG-01-lbhz-jumbo.jpg', '2025-08-01', '2025-08-01 07:24:37', '2025-08-05 18:14:27'),
(29, 'From Bikinis to Burkinis, Regulating What Women Wear!!!', 'from-bikinis-to-burkinis-regulating-what-women-wear', 'From Bikinis to Burkinis, Regulating What Women Wear', '<header class=\"css-16raiy2 e12qa4dv0\">\r\n<div class=\"css-1vkm6nb ehdk2mb0\">\r\n<h1 id=\"link-6781c7c4\" class=\"css-r25it4 e1h9rw200\" data-testid=\"headline\">From Bikinis to Burkinis, Regulating What Women Wear</h1>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"css-yomkvi\" role=\"toolbar\" data-testid=\"share-tools\" aria-label=\"Social Media Share buttons, Save button, and Comments Panel with current comment count\">\r\n<div class=\"css-17cfcd4\">&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div class=\"css-1q9ot06\" data-testid=\"share-tools-menu\">\r\n<ul class=\"css-16g9egj\" data-testid=\"share-tools-list\">\r\n<li class=\"css-1obgmli\">\r\n<div class=\"css-vxcmzt\">&nbsp;</div>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div data-testid=\"imageblock-wrapper\">\r\n<figure class=\"sizeMedium layoutVertical css-nlqgyf\" role=\"group\" aria-label=\"media\">\r\n<div class=\"css-1xb94ky\" data-testid=\"imageContainer-children-Image\"><img class=\"css-rq4mmj\" style=\"display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\" src=\"https://static01.nyt.com/images/2016/08/28/world/BURQINMEMO1/BURQINMEMO1-thumbLarge.jpg?quality=75&amp;auto=webp&amp;disable=upscale\" sizes=\"((min-width: 600px) and (max-width: 1004px)) 84vw, (min-width: 1005px) 60vw, 100vw\" srcset=\"https://static01.nyt.com/images/2016/08/28/world/BURQINMEMO1/BURQINMEMO1-articleLarge.jpg?quality=75&amp;auto=webp 600w,https://static01.nyt.com/images/2016/08/28/world/BURQINMEMO1/BURQINMEMO1-jumbo.jpg?quality=75&amp;auto=webp 762w,https://static01.nyt.com/images/2016/08/28/world/BURQINMEMO1/BURQINMEMO1-superJumbo.jpg?quality=75&amp;auto=webp 1523w\" alt=\"\" width=\"370\" height=\"370\"></div>\r\n<figcaption class=\"css-ktho12 e3rygrp0\" data-testid=\"photoviewer-children-ImageCaption\"><span class=\"css-jevhma e13ogyst0\">A police officer issuing a woman a ticket for wearing a bikini on a beach at Rimini, Italy, in 1957.</span><span class=\"css-14fe1uy e1z0qqy90\"><span class=\"css-1ly73wi e1tej78p0\">Credit...</span><span aria-hidden=\"false\">ullstein bild, via Akg-Images</span></span></figcaption>\r\n</figure>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"css-xt80pu eakwutd0\" data-testid=\"byline-timestamp\">\r\n<div class=\"css-p6m5rf\">\r\n<div class=\"byline-container css-1e2jphy epjyd6m2\">\r\n<div class=\"css-233int epjyd6m1\">\r\n<p class=\"css-4anu6l e1jsehar1\"><span class=\"byline-prefix\">By&nbsp;</span><a class=\"last-byline css-ojhyzr e1jsehar0\" itemprop=\"name\" href=\"https://www.nytimes.com/by/alissa-j-rubin\">Alissa J. Rubin</a></p>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<ul class=\"css-1cgskve epjyd6m4\">\r\n<li class=\"css-ccw2r3 epjyd6m3\"><time class=\"css-1uc6ajg e16638kd0\" datetime=\"2016-08-27T10:49:25-04:00\">Aug. 27, 2016</time></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</header>\r\n<section class=\"meteredContent css-ar1ez3\">\r\n<div class=\"css-s99gbd StoryBodyCompanionColumn\" data-testid=\"companionColumn-0\">\r\n<div class=\"css-53u6y8\">\r\n<p class=\"css-at9mc1 evys1bk0\">PARIS &mdash; The policeman in the photo is nattily attired and appears to have a slight smirk as he writes out a ticket for the woman standing before him awkwardly in her offending swimwear; perhaps he enjoys making her feel uncomfortable.</p>\r\n<p class=\"css-at9mc1 evys1bk0\">No, she is not wearing a burkini.</p>\r\n<p class=\"css-at9mc1 evys1bk0\">The photo dates from 1957. The woman is wearing a bikini on the beach at Rimini on Italy&rsquo;s Adriatic coast. At the time, Italy prohibited the revealing bathing suit; it was too immodest to be worn in public.</p>\r\n<p class=\"css-at9mc1 evys1bk0\">In the midst of France&rsquo;s fight over&nbsp;<a class=\"css-yywogo\" title=\"\" href=\"http://www.nytimes.com/2016/08/18/world/europe/fighting-for-the-soul-of-france-more-towns-ban-a-bathing-suit-the-burkini.html\">banning the burkini</a>, the bikini is celebrating its 70th anniversary, and photographs chronicling its debut and early history in the 1940s, &rsquo;50s and &rsquo;60s are on display in one of Paris&rsquo;s chic galleries, prompting parallels to the uproar over the burkini today.</p>\r\n<p class=\"css-at9mc1 evys1bk0\">What is it about women&rsquo;s swimwear and more generally women&rsquo;s attire that over and over in history has attracted controversy and impelled societies to legislate or regulate women&rsquo;s choices?</p>\r\n</div>\r\n<aside class=\"css-ew4tgv\" aria-label=\"companion column\"></aside>\r\n</div>\r\n<div data-testid=\"Dropzone-1\">\r\n<div id=\"story-ad-1-wrapper\" class=\"css-1w2m312\">\r\n<div id=\"story-ad-1-slug\" class=\"css-1ev7j75\">\r\n<p>Advertisement</p>\r\n</div>\r\n<div id=\"story-ad-1\" class=\"ad story-ad-1-wrapper css-rfqw0c\" data-google-query-id=\"CNWxmteK6Y4DFRyLgwcdN6kfWQ\">\r\n<div id=\"google_ads_iframe_/29390238/nyt/world/europe_3__container__\"></div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div id=\"after-story-ad-1\"></div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"css-s99gbd StoryBodyCompanionColumn\" data-testid=\"companionColumn-1\">\r\n<div class=\"css-53u6y8\">\r\n<p class=\"css-at9mc1 evys1bk0\">Historians, sociologists and anthropologists have argued about it for decades, but the seemingly simplistic statement that women&rsquo;s bodies are a battleground has some truth to it. Formally or informally, men (primarily) have been making rules about women&rsquo;s attire for a very long time.</p>\r\n<p class=\"css-at9mc1 evys1bk0\">&ldquo;Can&rsquo;t we decide what we want to wear in 2016?&rdquo; wondered Sarah Fekih, 23, from Lyon, France, in a comment she wrote to The New York Times. &ldquo;If one wishes to dress skimpily or to be almost nude or to be covered from head to toe, isn&rsquo;t that a personal choice that can not be dictated by law?&rdquo;</p>\r\n<p class=\"css-at9mc1 evys1bk0\">Of course, the burkini debate is not only about feminism. It is foremost a debate about the visibility and presence of Islam in France, and it comes in the context of the most recent act of terror to traumatize the country, this one in Nice, on the Mediterranean coast.</p>\r\n<p class=\"css-at9mc1 evys1bk0\">On July 14, a man&nbsp;<a class=\"css-yywogo\" title=\"\" href=\"http://www.nytimes.com/2016/07/16/world/europe/attack-nice-bastille-day.html?_r=0\">drove a cargo truck</a>&nbsp;into crowds of people there, killing 86 and wounding 300. The Islamic State later called him one of its &ldquo;soldiers.&rdquo;</p>\r\n<p class=\"css-at9mc1 evys1bk0\">Less than a month later, the first of at least 30 bans on &ldquo;inappropriate&rdquo; clothing on beaches &mdash; meant to target Muslim attire &mdash; was&nbsp;<a class=\"css-yywogo\" title=\"\" href=\"http://www.nytimes.com/2016/08/13/world/europe/cannes-muslims-burkini-ban.html\">enacted in Cannes</a>, about 20 miles from Nice.</p>\r\n</div>\r\n<aside class=\"css-ew4tgv\" aria-label=\"companion column\">\r\n<div id=\"c-col-editors-picks\" class=\"css-lze5f4\"></div>\r\n</aside>\r\n</div>\r\n<div data-testid=\"Dropzone-3\">\r\n<div id=\"story-ad-2-wrapper\" class=\"css-1w2m312\">\r\n<div id=\"story-ad-2\" class=\"ad story-ad-2-wrapper css-rfqw0c\" data-google-query-id=\"CICN8teK6Y4DFSClgwcdjWcPhQ\">\r\n<div id=\"google_ads_iframe_/29390238/nyt/world/europe_4__container__\"></div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div id=\"after-story-ad-2\"></div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"css-s99gbd StoryBodyCompanionColumn\" data-testid=\"companionColumn-2\">\r\n<div class=\"css-53u6y8\">\r\n<p class=\"css-at9mc1 evys1bk0\">Although France&rsquo;s highest administrative court, the Council of State,&nbsp;<a class=\"css-yywogo\" title=\"\" href=\"http://www.nytimes.com/2016/08/27/world/europe/france-burkini-ban.html\">struck down</a>&nbsp;one town&rsquo;s burkini ban on Friday &mdash; and clearly would do the same for other towns if lawsuits were brought &mdash; the fight is far from over.</p>\r\n</div>\r\n<aside class=\"css-ew4tgv\" aria-label=\"companion column\"></aside>\r\n</div>\r\n<div data-testid=\"ImageBlock-5\">\r\n<div data-testid=\"imageblock-wrapper\">\r\n<figure class=\"img-sz-medium css-1hs5yzu e1g7ppur0\" role=\"group\" aria-label=\"media\">\r\n<div class=\"css-1xdhyk6 erfvjey0\" data-testid=\"photoviewer-children-figure\"><span class=\"css-1ly73wi e1tej78p0\">Image</span>\r\n<div class=\"css-1pq3dr9\" data-testid=\"lazy-image\">\r\n<div data-testid=\"lazyimage-container\"><img class=\"css-1m50asq\" src=\"https://static01.nyt.com/images/2016/08/28/world/BURQUINIMEMO2/BURQUINIMEMO2-articleInline.jpg?quality=75&amp;auto=webp&amp;disable=upscale\" sizes=\"((min-width: 600px) and (max-width: 1004px)) 84vw, (min-width: 1005px) 60vw, 100vw\" srcset=\"https://static01.nyt.com/images/2016/08/28/world/BURQUINIMEMO2/BURQUINIMEMO2-articleLarge.jpg?quality=75&amp;auto=webp 600w,https://static01.nyt.com/images/2016/08/28/world/BURQUINIMEMO2/BURQUINIMEMO2-jumbo.jpg?quality=75&amp;auto=webp 870w,https://static01.nyt.com/images/2016/08/28/world/BURQUINIMEMO2/BURQUINIMEMO2-superJumbo.jpg?quality=75&amp;auto=webp 1686w\" alt=\"\" loading=\"lazy\"></div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<figcaption class=\"css-gbc9ki ewdxa0s0\" data-testid=\"photoviewer-children-caption\"><span class=\"css-jevhma e13ogyst0\">Armed police officers forced a woman to remove her shirt on a beach in Nice, France, on Tuesday after a ban on burkinis went into effect.</span><span class=\"css-14fe1uy e1z0qqy90\"><span class=\"css-1ly73wi e1tej78p0\">Credit...</span><span aria-hidden=\"false\">BestImage</span></span></figcaption>\r\n</figure>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"css-s99gbd StoryBodyCompanionColumn\" data-testid=\"companionColumn-3\">\r\n<div class=\"css-53u6y8\">\r\n<p class=\"css-at9mc1 evys1bk0\">The Parliament could enact a ban, and some of France&rsquo;s 2017 presidential candidates on the right and far right have pledged to enact measures that run from banning the Muslim veil in universities and businesses to banning almost all religious attire in public.</p>\r\n<p class=\"css-at9mc1 evys1bk0\">As the debate continues, much that is important will be said about France and racism and Islam, but it is worth pondering that it is women&rsquo;s clothes that are at issue.</p>\r\n<p class=\"css-at9mc1 evys1bk0\">Throughout history, a combination of legislation, local regulation and social pressure has influenced the way women have dressed &mdash; corsets and d&eacute;collet&eacute;, hoop skirts and bustles, the controversial advent of pants. France is now a society demanding that women undress, but in many ways this debate is part of the same narrative.</p>\r\n</div>\r\n<aside class=\"css-ew4tgv\" aria-label=\"companion column\"></aside>\r\n</div>\r\n<div data-testid=\"Dropzone-7\">\r\n<div id=\"story-ad-3-wrapper\" class=\"css-1w2m312\"></div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"css-s99gbd StoryBodyCompanionColumn\" data-testid=\"companionColumn-4\">\r\n<div class=\"css-53u6y8\">\r\n<p class=\"css-at9mc1 evys1bk0\">In the case of both the bikini and the burkini, &ldquo;people in positions of power say, &lsquo;We&rsquo;re putting these rules in place for the woman&rsquo;s good,&rsquo;&rdquo; said Deirdre Clemente, a history professor at the University of Nevada who has studied dress codes for women. &ldquo;The implication is that women are unable to regulate their appearance themselves.&rdquo;</p>\r\n<p class=\"css-at9mc1 evys1bk0\">As recently as the 1980s, a number of large American corporations had extensive dress codes for women. &ldquo;There would be four pages on what a woman could wear to work, and four sentences for men,&rdquo; Professor Clemente said.</p>\r\n<p class=\"css-at9mc1 evys1bk0\">When it came to the bikini, not only was it forbidden in some countries, with women forced to pay fines and leave many beaches if they wore one. It was also seen as subversive and a sign of moral weakness.</p>\r\n<p class=\"css-at9mc1 evys1bk0\">Italy, Spain and some beaches on the Atlantic coast of France prohibited wearing the swimsuit in the first few years after it went on the market, said Ghislaine Rayer, a co-author of &ldquo;Bikini: La L&eacute;gende,&rdquo; a history of the mini-swimsuit.</p>\r\n<p class=\"css-at9mc1 evys1bk0\">That prohibition resonates in today&rsquo;s burkini debate, said Hanane Karimi, a graduate student of sociology at the University of Strasbourg. She is the leader of a feminist Muslim collective that wants mosques in France to make more space for women at prayers and to be more respectful of their involvement in religious affairs</p>\r\n<p class=\"css-at9mc1 evys1bk0\">&ldquo;In some countries that had strong religiosity, like Italy, controlling women&rsquo;s bodies was a part of the country&rsquo;s religious morality; today in France there is a civil religion of secularity,&rdquo; she said. &ldquo;And it has the exact same logic in respect to the control of women&rsquo;s bodies: Those women who adhere to that secular morality are undressed on the beaches; nothing is hidden.&rdquo;</p>\r\n</div>\r\n<aside class=\"css-ew4tgv\" aria-label=\"companion column\"></aside>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"css-s99gbd StoryBodyCompanionColumn\" data-testid=\"companionColumn-5\">\r\n<div class=\"css-53u6y8\">\r\n<p class=\"css-at9mc1 evys1bk0\">Today the French seem to believe as strongly that such undress is mandatory as Italy, under the Vatican&rsquo;s influence, felt it was necessary to hide women&rsquo;s bodies, she added.</p>\r\n<p class=\"css-at9mc1 evys1bk0\">It was not always that way. When the designer of the first bikini, Louis R&eacute;ard, coined the name (a play on the tiny atoll of Bikini, where the United States had just tested the atomic bomb) and showed his new swimsuit at the Molitor Pool in Paris on July 5, 1946, he could not find models willing to wear it.</p>\r\n<p class=\"css-at9mc1 evys1bk0\">So he hired dancer-strippers from the Paris Casino. &ldquo;It was avant-garde; it was ahead of its time,&rdquo; said Ms. Rayer, the co-author of the book on the bikini&rsquo;s history. &ldquo;In that epoch, we were still puritan.&rdquo;</p>\r\n<p class=\"css-at9mc1 evys1bk0\">Although the bikini quickly became popular in movies, it took more than 15 years, and longer in many places, to enter the fashion mainstream. France embraced it ahead of several other countries and eventually even allowed women to sunbathe or swim toples</p>\r\n<p class=\"css-at9mc1 evys1bk0\">Joan Wallach Scott, a social scientist at the Institute for Advanced Study in Princeton, sees France&rsquo;s approbation of revealing swimwear, as well as the current burkini bans, as products of ideas going back to the French Revolution of 1789.</p>\r\n</div>\r\n<aside class=\"css-ew4tgv\" aria-label=\"companion column\"></aside>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"css-s99gbd StoryBodyCompanionColumn\" data-testid=\"companionColumn-6\">\r\n<div class=\"css-53u6y8\">\r\n<p class=\"css-at9mc1 evys1bk0\">&ldquo;What you have in French republicanism is a conflict between a commitment to equality and the notion that sexual difference is a natural difference which explains why there can&rsquo;t be equality between women and men,&rdquo; she said.</p>\r\n<p class=\"css-at9mc1 evys1bk0\">The French believe it is necessary to show the difference between men and women physically even while proclaiming their equality, Ms. Scott said.</p>\r\n<p class=\"css-at9mc1 evys1bk0\">The painter Eug&egrave;ne Delacroix depicted &ldquo;Liberty&rdquo; as a bare-breasted woman leading the righteous French. Sculptures and reliefs of a bare-breasted or semi-bare-breasted Marianne, a French symbol of the revolution and liberty, can still be found on government documents, buildings and postal stamps. The very depiction of women reflects how the sexes differ.</p>\r\n</div>\r\n<aside class=\"css-ew4tgv\" aria-label=\"companion column\"></aside>\r\n</div>\r\n<div data-testid=\"Dropzone-13\">\r\n<div id=\"story-ad-6-wrapper\" class=\"css-n0pgz9\">\r\n<div id=\"story-ad-6-slug\" class=\"css-1ev7j75\"></div>\r\n<div id=\"story-ad-6\" class=\"ad story-ad-6-wrapper css-rfqw0c\" data-google-query-id=\"CPCrp9qK6Y4DFRmJgwcdLHsu3A\">\r\n<div id=\"google_ads_iframe_/29390238/nyt/world/europe_8__container__\">&ldquo;Then on the other side you have Muslim society saying that sex and sexual difference is a problem, and women, whether submitting or not, are covered. So in a sense they are exposing the contradiction in French society, and that&rsquo;s intolerable,&rdquo; Ms. Scott said. &ldquo;It becomes a commentary on the French need to have women uncovered.&rdquo;</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div id=\"after-story-ad-6\"></div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"css-s99gbd StoryBodyCompanionColumn\" data-testid=\"companionColumn-7\">\r\n<div class=\"css-53u6y8\">\r\n<p class=\"css-at9mc1 evys1bk0\">Indeed, the deputy mayor of Nice, Christian Estrosi, who is a political power broker on the C&ocirc;te d&rsquo;Azur, has repeatedly referred to the covering of women on the beach &mdash; whether in a burkini or a large T-shirt, pants and hijab &mdash; as a &ldquo;provocation,&rdquo; suggesting a challenge to the French order.</p>\r\n<p class=\"css-at9mc1 evys1bk0\">Such language mystifies one of the burkini&rsquo;s designers, who sells her pieces in France. Vanessa Louren&ccedil;o, the designer, said she had started creating them to give Muslim women a chance to participate in the same activities as the rest of the community.</p>\r\n<p class=\"css-at9mc1 evys1bk0\">She loves to swim herself, she said, so seeing religious Muslims or other people not go swimming &ldquo;struck me as unacceptable.&rdquo;</p>\r\n<p class=\"css-at9mc1 evys1bk0\">Ms. Louren&ccedil;o, whose internet business sells swimwear in 120 countries, is not Muslim, and people often ask her why she designs for Muslim women.</p>\r\n</div>\r\n<aside class=\"css-ew4tgv\" aria-label=\"companion column\"></aside>\r\n</div>\r\n<div data-testid=\"Dropzone-15\">\r\n<div id=\"story-ad-7-wrapper\" class=\"css-n0pgz9\">\r\n<div id=\"story-ad-7-slug\" class=\"css-1ev7j75\"></div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"css-s99gbd StoryBodyCompanionColumn\" data-testid=\"companionColumn-8\">\r\n<div class=\"css-53u6y8\">\r\n<p class=\"css-at9mc1 evys1bk0\">&ldquo;My answer is simple: At the end of the day women are women, whether Muslim or not, and we all want to be comfortable, look beautiful and feel feminine,&rdquo; she said.</p>\r\n<p class=\"css-at9mc1 evys1bk0\">&ldquo;Most of our clients message us saying it is the first time that they were confident enough to be at a public beach enjoying themselves with their family.&rdquo;</p>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</section>', '', '/uploads/3bd811ba-a3ac-48aa-aa3c-142b8231160e_BURQINMEMO1-superJumbo.jpg', '2025-08-01', '2025-08-01 07:29:00', '2025-08-01 10:43:55'),
(30, 'E.U. Did Not Retain Texts Sought by Journalists on Covid Vaccine Deal', 'eu-did-not-retain-texts-sought-by-journalists-on-covid-vaccine-deal', 'E.U. Did Not Retain Texts Sought by Journalists on Covid Vaccine Deal', '<header class=\"css-1qv3lay euiyums1\">\r\n<div class=\"css-1vkm6nb ehdk2mb0\">\r\n<h1 id=\"link-5d2da84e\" class=\"css-88wicj e1h9rw200\" data-testid=\"headline\">E.U. Did Not Retain Texts Sought by Journalists on Covid Vaccine Deal</h1>\r\n</div>\r\n<p id=\"article-summary\" class=\"css-79rysd e1wiw3jv0\">The European Union acknowledged for the first time that a top official reviewed the messages, but said it had no duty to keep them, despite intense interest.</p>\r\n<div class=\"css-qznc1j\">\r\n<div class=\"css-1e4xg23\">\r\n<div class=\"css-1von7hd\">\r\n<div class=\"css-b8gc4a\">\r\n<div class=\"css-79elbk\">&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div class=\"css-uepebd\">\r\n<div class=\"css-35ezg3\">Listen to this article&nbsp;&middot; 6:09 min&nbsp;<span class=\"css-14h5vr8\"><a href=\"https://help.nytimes.com/hc/en-us/articles/24318293692180\">Learn more</a></span></div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"css-1pec0v7\">\r\n<div class=\"css-yomkvi\" role=\"toolbar\" data-testid=\"share-tools\" aria-label=\"Social Media Share buttons, Save button, and Comments Panel with current comment count\">\r\n<div class=\"css-17cfcd4\">&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div class=\"css-ac2f9k\" data-testid=\"share-tools-menu\">\r\n<ul class=\"css-16g9egj\" data-testid=\"share-tools-list\">\r\n<li class=\"css-1obgmli\">\r\n<div class=\"css-vxcmzt\">\r\n<div class=\"css-79elbk\"><button class=\"css-1eeh360 actionbar-button\" type=\"button\" aria-label=\"\" aria-expanded=\"false\" data-testid=\"gift-article-button\"><span class=\"css-10d8k1f\">Share full article</span></button></div>\r\n</div>\r\n</li>\r\n<li class=\"css-19yhb3c\">\r\n<div class=\"css-vxcmzt\">\r\n<div class=\"css-79elbk\">&nbsp;</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</li>\r\n<li class=\"css-19yhb3c save-button\">&nbsp;</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div data-testid=\"imageblock-wrapper\">\r\n<figure class=\"sizeMedium layoutHorizontal css-nlqgyf\" role=\"group\" aria-label=\"media\">\r\n<div class=\"css-1xb94ky\" data-testid=\"imageContainer-children-Image\"><picture><source srcset=\"https://static01.nyt.com/images/2025/07/31/multimedia/31eu-texts-001-wvgc/31eu-texts-001-wvgc-mobileMasterAt3x.jpg?quality=75&amp;auto=webp&amp;disable=upscale&amp;width=1800\" media=\"(max-width: 599px) and (min-device-pixel-ratio: 3),(max-width: 599px) and (min-resolution: 3dppx),(max-width: 599px) and (min-resolution: 288dpi)\"><source srcset=\"https://static01.nyt.com/images/2025/07/31/multimedia/31eu-texts-001-wvgc/31eu-texts-001-wvgc-mobileMasterAt3x.jpg?quality=75&amp;auto=webp&amp;disable=upscale&amp;width=1200\" media=\"(max-width: 599px) and (min-device-pixel-ratio: 2),(max-width: 599px) and (min-resolution: 2dppx),(max-width: 599px) and (min-resolution: 192dpi)\"><source srcset=\"https://static01.nyt.com/images/2025/07/31/multimedia/31eu-texts-001-wvgc/31eu-texts-001-wvgc-mobileMasterAt3x.jpg?quality=75&amp;auto=webp&amp;disable=upscale&amp;width=600\" media=\"(max-width: 599px) and (min-device-pixel-ratio: 1),(max-width: 599px) and (min-resolution: 1dppx),(max-width: 599px) and (min-resolution: 96dpi)\"><img class=\"css-rq4mmj\" src=\"https://static01.nyt.com/images/2025/07/31/multimedia/31eu-texts-001-wvgc/31eu-texts-001-wvgc-articleLarge.jpg?quality=75&amp;auto=webp&amp;disable=upscale\" sizes=\"((min-width: 600px) and (max-width: 1004px)) 84vw, (min-width: 1005px) 60vw, 100vw\" srcset=\"https://static01.nyt.com/images/2025/07/31/multimedia/31eu-texts-001-wvgc/31eu-texts-001-wvgc-articleLarge.jpg?quality=75&amp;auto=webp 600w,https://static01.nyt.com/images/2025/07/31/multimedia/31eu-texts-001-wvgc/31eu-texts-001-wvgc-jumbo.jpg?quality=75&amp;auto=webp 1024w,https://static01.nyt.com/images/2025/07/31/multimedia/31eu-texts-001-wvgc/31eu-texts-001-wvgc-superJumbo.jpg?quality=75&amp;auto=webp 2048w\" alt=\"Ursula von der Leyen.\" width=\"600\" height=\"401\"></picture></div>\r\n<figcaption class=\"css-ktho12 e3rygrp0\" data-testid=\"photoviewer-children-ImageCaption\"><span class=\"css-jevhma e13ogyst0\">Ursula von der Leyen, the president of the European Commission, in London, in March.</span><span class=\"css-14fe1uy e1z0qqy90\"><span class=\"css-1ly73wi e1tej78p0\">Credit...</span><span aria-hidden=\"false\">Pool photo by Toby Melville</span></span></figcaption>\r\n</figure>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"css-p6m5rf\">\r\n<div class=\"byline-container css-1u5onbp epjyd6m2\">\r\n<div class=\"css-165eim7 ey68jwv0\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><a class=\"css-uwwqev\" href=\"https://www.nytimes.com/by/jeanna-smialek\"><img class=\"css-dc6zx6 ey68jwv2\" title=\"Jeanna Smialek\" src=\"https://static01.nyt.com/images/2020/07/03/reader-center/author-jeanna-smialek/author-jeanna-smialek-thumbLarge-v2.png\" alt=\"Jeanna Smialek\"></a></div>\r\n<div class=\"css-233int epjyd6m1\">\r\n<p class=\"css-4anu6l e1jsehar1\"><span class=\"byline-prefix\">By&nbsp;</span><a class=\"last-byline css-ojhyzr e1jsehar0\" itemprop=\"name\" href=\"https://www.nytimes.com/by/jeanna-smialek\">Jeanna Smialek</a></p>\r\n<div class=\"css-17nm0qx epjyd6m0\">\r\n<div id=\"enhanced-byline\" class=\"css-8atqhb\">\r\n<p class=\"css-1hyokyd e1wtpvyy0\">Reporting from Brussels</p>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"css-1c72mta\"><time class=\"css-kx0gap e16638kd0\" datetime=\"2025-08-01T00:01:06-04:00\">Aug. 1, 2025,&nbsp;<span class=\"css-epvm6\">12:01 a.m. ET</span></time></div>\r\n</header>\r\n<section class=\"meteredContent css-ar1ez3\">\r\n<div class=\"css-s99gbd StoryBodyCompanionColumn\" data-testid=\"companionColumn-0\">\r\n<div class=\"css-53u6y8\">\r\n<p class=\"css-at9mc1 evys1bk0\">When the European Union&nbsp;<a class=\"css-yywogo\" title=\"\" href=\"https://www.nytimes.com/2021/04/28/world/europe/european-union-pfizer-von-der-leyen-coronavirus-vaccine.html\">secured a deal</a>&nbsp;to purchase up to 1.8 billion doses of Pfizer&rsquo;s coronavirus vaccine in early 2021, there was great interest in how the bloc had managed to clinch an agreement seen as a major victory.</p>\r\n<p class=\"css-at9mc1 evys1bk0\">So when it&nbsp;<a class=\"css-yywogo\" title=\"\" href=\"https://www.nytimes.com/2021/04/28/world/the-eu-seals-a-deal-with-pfizer-to-speed-up-vaccinations.html\">came to light</a>&nbsp;that Ursula von der Leyen, president of the E.U. executive branch, had traded text messages with Pfizer&rsquo;s chief executive while negotiating the deal, journalists were quick to ask for those records under the bloc&rsquo;s transparency rules. The European Union refused, and The New York Times challenged that refusal in court.</p>\r\n<p class=\"css-at9mc1 evys1bk0\">This May,&nbsp;<a class=\"css-yywogo\" title=\"\" href=\"https://www.nytimes.com/2025/05/14/world/europe/eu-texts-covid-new-york-times.html\">an E.U. court ruled</a>&nbsp;that the bloc had &ldquo;failed to explain in a plausible manner&rdquo; why it had not released the records. In response to that ruling, the bloc&rsquo;s executive branch, the European Commission, this week gave The Times a more detailed account, but it may do little to soothe the concerns of transparency activists, for whom the protracted battle has become a flashpoint.</p>\r\n<p class=\"css-at9mc1 evys1bk0\">The commission&rsquo;s response implies that it destroyed or lost the messages after judging that they were not important and it had no obligation to keep them.</p>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</section>', '', '/uploads/2c712209-582c-44b3-bdbf-3e064600746c_31eu-texts-001-wvgc-articleLarge.jpg', '2025-08-01', '2025-08-01 07:30:27', '2025-08-01 07:30:27');
INSERT INTO `posts` (`id`, `title`, `slug`, `excerpt`, `content`, `category`, `image_url`, `published_at`, `created_at`, `updated_at`) VALUES
(31, 'Robbery of U.K. Royal Family’s Items Leads to $4 Million Insurance Payment', 'robbery-of-uk-royal-familys-items-leads-to-4-million-insurance-payment', 'Robbery of U.K. Royal Family’s Items Leads to $4 Million Insurance Payment', '<div class=\"css-1vkm6nb ehdk2mb0\">\r\n<h1 id=\"link-201e9bd8\" class=\"css-1uc375s e1h9rw200\" data-testid=\"headline\">Robbery of U.K. Royal Family&rsquo;s Items Leads to $4 Million Insurance Payment</h1>\r\n</div>\r\n<p id=\"article-summary\" class=\"css-79rysd e1wiw3jv0\">Two centuries-old snuff boxes adorned with diamonds and gold were among several artifacts stolen in a violent museum heist in Paris last year.</p>\r\n<header class=\"css-1stea7k euiyums1\">\r\n<div class=\"css-qznc1j\">\r\n<div class=\"css-1e4xg23\">\r\n<div class=\"css-1von7hd\">\r\n<div class=\"css-b8gc4a\">\r\n<div class=\"css-uepebd\">&nbsp;</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"css-1pec0v7\">\r\n<div class=\"css-yomkvi\" role=\"toolbar\" data-testid=\"share-tools\" aria-label=\"Social Media Share buttons, Save button, and Comments Panel with current comment count\">\r\n<div class=\"css-ac2f9k\" data-testid=\"share-tools-menu\">\r\n<ul class=\"css-16g9egj\" data-testid=\"share-tools-list\">\r\n<li class=\"css-1obgmli\">\r\n<div class=\"css-vxcmzt\">&nbsp;</div>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div data-testid=\"imageblock-wrapper\">\r\n<figure class=\"sizeLarge layoutHorizontal css-nlqgyf\" role=\"group\" aria-label=\"media\">\r\n<div class=\"css-1xb94ky\" data-testid=\"imageContainer-children-Image\"><picture><source srcset=\"https://static01.nyt.com/images/2025/07/31/multimedia/31cul-royals-theft-02-hwqv/31cul-royals-theft-02-hwqv-mobileMasterAt3x.jpg?quality=75&amp;auto=webp&amp;disable=upscale&amp;width=1800\" media=\"(max-width: 599px) and (min-device-pixel-ratio: 3),(max-width: 599px) and (min-resolution: 3dppx),(max-width: 599px) and (min-resolution: 288dpi)\"><source srcset=\"https://static01.nyt.com/images/2025/07/31/multimedia/31cul-royals-theft-02-hwqv/31cul-royals-theft-02-hwqv-mobileMasterAt3x.jpg?quality=75&amp;auto=webp&amp;disable=upscale&amp;width=1200\" media=\"(max-width: 599px) and (min-device-pixel-ratio: 2),(max-width: 599px) and (min-resolution: 2dppx),(max-width: 599px) and (min-resolution: 192dpi)\"><source srcset=\"https://static01.nyt.com/images/2025/07/31/multimedia/31cul-royals-theft-02-hwqv/31cul-royals-theft-02-hwqv-mobileMasterAt3x.jpg?quality=75&amp;auto=webp&amp;disable=upscale&amp;width=600\" media=\"(max-width: 599px) and (min-device-pixel-ratio: 1),(max-width: 599px) and (min-resolution: 1dppx),(max-width: 599px) and (min-resolution: 96dpi)\"><img class=\"css-rq4mmj\" src=\"https://static01.nyt.com/images/2025/07/31/multimedia/31cul-royals-theft-02-hwqv/31cul-royals-theft-02-hwqv-articleLarge.jpg?quality=75&amp;auto=webp&amp;disable=upscale\" sizes=\"((min-width: 600px) and (max-width: 1004px)) 84vw, (min-width: 1005px) 80vw, 100vw\" srcset=\"https://static01.nyt.com/images/2025/07/31/multimedia/31cul-royals-theft-02-hwqv/31cul-royals-theft-02-hwqv-articleLarge.jpg?quality=75&amp;auto=webp 600w,https://static01.nyt.com/images/2025/07/31/multimedia/31cul-royals-theft-02-hwqv/31cul-royals-theft-02-hwqv-jumbo.jpg?quality=75&amp;auto=webp 1024w,https://static01.nyt.com/images/2025/07/31/multimedia/31cul-royals-theft-02-hwqv/31cul-royals-theft-02-hwqv-superJumbo.jpg?quality=75&amp;auto=webp 2000w\" alt=\"A close-up image of a diamond encrusted snuff box.\" width=\"600\" height=\"480\"></picture></div>\r\n<figcaption class=\"css-ktho12 e3rygrp0\" data-testid=\"photoviewer-children-ImageCaption\"><span class=\"css-jevhma e13ogyst0\">A table snuff box, originally used to hold powdered tobacco, encrusted with almost 3,000 diamonds. It is one of the two snuff boxes that were stolen from the Mus&eacute;e Cognacq-Jay in Paris last year.</span><span class=\"css-14fe1uy e1z0qqy90\"><span class=\"css-1ly73wi e1tej78p0\">Credit...</span><span aria-hidden=\"false\">via Royal Collection Enterprises Limited 2025/Royal Collection Trust</span></span></figcaption>\r\n</figure>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"css-p6m5rf\">\r\n<div class=\"byline-container css-1e2jphy epjyd6m2\">\r\n<div class=\"css-233int epjyd6m1\">\r\n<p class=\"css-4anu6l e1jsehar1\"><span class=\"byline-prefix\">By&nbsp;</span><a class=\"last-byline css-ojhyzr e1jsehar0\" itemprop=\"name\" href=\"https://www.nytimes.com/by/lizzie-dearden\">Lizzie Dearden</a></p>\r\n<div class=\"css-4q3lf8 epjyd6m0\">\r\n<div id=\"enhanced-byline\" class=\"css-8atqhb\">\r\n<p class=\"css-1hyokyd e1wtpvyy0\">Reporting from London</p>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"css-1c72mta\"><time class=\"css-kx0gap e16638kd0\" datetime=\"2025-07-31T13:10:53-04:00\">July 31, 2025</time></div>\r\n</header>\r\n<section class=\"meteredContent css-ar1ez3\">\r\n<div class=\"css-s99gbd StoryBodyCompanionColumn\" data-testid=\"companionColumn-0\">\r\n<div class=\"css-53u6y8\">\r\n<p class=\"css-at9mc1 evys1bk0\">The organization that manages the British royal family&rsquo;s art collection received an insurance payment of &pound;3 million, about $4 million, after thieves stole two of its artifacts that were on loan to a Paris museum, the organization has disclosed.</p>\r\n<p class=\"css-at9mc1 evys1bk0\">The two pieces, both elaborate snuff boxes that were originally used to hold powdered tobacco, included one that was encrusted with almost 3,000 diamonds and another that was decorated with gold and depicted the birth of the Roman goddess Venus.</p>\r\n<p class=\"css-at9mc1 evys1bk0\">Both had been on loan to the Mus&eacute;e Cognacq-Jay in Paris for its &ldquo;pocket luxury&rdquo; exhibition, which opened in March last year with a collection of opulently decorated historical fashion accessories. But on the morning of Nov. 20,&nbsp;<a class=\"css-yywogo\" title=\"\" href=\"https://presse.paris.fr/press_releases/9774\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">according to the Paris police</a>, robbers carried out a violent daytime heist in front of visitors and employees.</p>\r\n<p class=\"css-at9mc1 evys1bk0\">A&nbsp;<a class=\"css-yywogo\" title=\"\" href=\"https://www.lemonde.fr/en/culture/article/2024/12/10/musee-cognacq-jay-in-paris-reopens-a-few-days-after-a-robbery_6735891_30.html\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">report in the French daily Le Monde</a> outlined how the robbers sped into the museum&rsquo;s courtyard on scooters and threatened a security guard with an ax before smashing a display case and grabbing several of the items inside.</p>\r\n<div class=\"css-s99gbd StoryBodyCompanionColumn\" data-testid=\"companionColumn-1\">\r\n<div class=\"css-53u6y8\">\r\n<p class=\"css-at9mc1 evys1bk0\">The two royal snuff boxes were found to be among the stolen artifacts, according to the museum. They were on loan from the Royal Collection Trust, which controls the royal family&rsquo;s art collection, and the trust&rsquo;s annual&nbsp;<a class=\"css-yywogo\" title=\"\" href=\"https://media.rct.uk/sites/default/files/2025-07/financial-statements-2024-25.pdf?_ga=2.97075740.2087659979.1753893439-1308962096.1753722570\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">financial report</a>&nbsp;revealed the resulting &pound;3 million insurance payout.</p>\r\n<p class=\"css-at9mc1 evys1bk0\">&ldquo;During the year, an insurance settlement was received in respect of snuff boxes stolen whilst on loan to the Mus&eacute;e Cognacq-Jay,&rdquo; the report said, adding that the money had been placed into a fund &ldquo;to be used for the enhancement of the Collection.&rdquo;</p>\r\n</div>\r\n<aside class=\"css-ew4tgv\" aria-label=\"companion column\"></aside>\r\n</div>\r\n<div data-testid=\"ImageBlock-3\">\r\n<div data-testid=\"imageblock-wrapper\">\r\n<figure class=\"img-sz-medium css-d754w4 e1g7ppur0\" role=\"group\" aria-label=\"media\">\r\n<div class=\"css-1xdhyk6 erfvjey0\" data-testid=\"photoviewer-children-figure\"><span class=\"css-1ly73wi e1tej78p0\">Image</span>\r\n<div class=\"css-1pq3dr9\" data-testid=\"lazy-image\">\r\n<div data-testid=\"lazyimage-container\"><picture class=\"css-1j5kxti\"><source srcset=\"https://static01.nyt.com/images/2025/07/31/multimedia/31cul-royals-theft-01-hwqv/31cul-royals-theft-01-hwqv-mobileMasterAt3x.jpg?quality=75&amp;auto=webp&amp;disable=upscale&amp;width=1800\" media=\"(max-width: 599px) and (min-device-pixel-ratio: 3),(max-width: 599px) and (min-resolution: 3dppx),(max-width: 599px) and (min-resolution: 288dpi)\"><source srcset=\"https://static01.nyt.com/images/2025/07/31/multimedia/31cul-royals-theft-01-hwqv/31cul-royals-theft-01-hwqv-mobileMasterAt3x.jpg?quality=75&amp;auto=webp&amp;disable=upscale&amp;width=1200\" media=\"(max-width: 599px) and (min-device-pixel-ratio: 2),(max-width: 599px) and (min-resolution: 2dppx),(max-width: 599px) and (min-resolution: 192dpi)\"><source srcset=\"https://static01.nyt.com/images/2025/07/31/multimedia/31cul-royals-theft-01-hwqv/31cul-royals-theft-01-hwqv-mobileMasterAt3x.jpg?quality=75&amp;auto=webp&amp;disable=upscale&amp;width=600\" media=\"(max-width: 599px) and (min-device-pixel-ratio: 1),(max-width: 599px) and (min-resolution: 1dppx),(max-width: 599px) and (min-resolution: 96dpi)\"><img class=\"css-1m50asq\" src=\"https://static01.nyt.com/images/2025/07/31/multimedia/31cul-royals-theft-01-hwqv/31cul-royals-theft-01-hwqv-articleLarge.jpg?quality=75&amp;auto=webp&amp;disable=upscale\" sizes=\"((min-width: 600px) and (max-width: 1004px)) 84vw, (min-width: 1005px) 60vw, 100vw\" srcset=\"https://static01.nyt.com/images/2025/07/31/multimedia/31cul-royals-theft-01-hwqv/31cul-royals-theft-01-hwqv-articleLarge.jpg?quality=75&amp;auto=webp 600w,https://static01.nyt.com/images/2025/07/31/multimedia/31cul-royals-theft-01-hwqv/31cul-royals-theft-01-hwqv-jumbo.jpg?quality=75&amp;auto=webp 1024w,https://static01.nyt.com/images/2025/07/31/multimedia/31cul-royals-theft-01-hwqv/31cul-royals-theft-01-hwqv-superJumbo.jpg?quality=75&amp;auto=webp 2048w\" alt=\"A blue and gold snuff box with a cameo of Venus in the center.\" loading=\"lazy\"></picture></div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<figcaption class=\"css-gbc9ki ewdxa0s0\" data-testid=\"photoviewer-children-caption\"><span class=\"css-jevhma e13ogyst0\">The other stolen box, decorated with gold and depicting the birth of the Roman goddess Venus.</span><span class=\"css-14fe1uy e1z0qqy90\"><span class=\"css-1ly73wi e1tej78p0\">Credit...</span><span aria-hidden=\"false\">via Royal Collection Enterprises Limited 2025/Royal Collection Trust</span></span></figcaption>\r\n</figure>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"css-s99gbd StoryBodyCompanionColumn\" data-testid=\"companionColumn-2\">\r\n<div class=\"css-53u6y8\">\r\n<p class=\"css-at9mc1 evys1bk0\">Also taken in the robbery were two snuff boxes belonging to the Louvre Museum in Paris and three that were on loan to the Victoria and Albert Museum of London, according to the trust.</p>\r\n<p class=\"css-at9mc1 evys1bk0\">The trust&rsquo;s website details how European jewelers began to make luxurious boxes in the 1600s as the practice of using snuff became increasingly fashionable, and the two stolen artifacts were part of a wider collection of such items held by British royals.</p>\r\n<p class=\"css-at9mc1 evys1bk0\">One of the stolen boxes dates from the 1700s and was previously owned by Russia&rsquo;s ruling Romanov family, but was confiscated by the Soviet authorities after the revolution and was eventually purchased by Queen Mary, King Charles III&rsquo;s great-grandmother. The Royal Collection Trust&nbsp;<a class=\"css-yywogo\" title=\"\" href=\"https://www.rct.uk/collection/stories/diamonds-in-the-royal-collection/table-snuff-box\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">describes it as a &ldquo;spectacular bloodstone box&rdquo;</a>&nbsp;and one of the finest German-made boxes of its kind.</p>\r\n<p class=\"css-at9mc1 evys1bk0\">The other stolen box was given to King George V as a birthday present in 1920, and is made of gold and lapis lazuli, with an onyx cameo depicting the birth of Venus,&nbsp;<a class=\"css-yywogo\" title=\"\" href=\"https://www.rct.uk/collection/4075/snuff-box-with-a-cameo-of-the-birth-of-venus\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">according to the trust&rsquo;s website</a>.</p>\r\n<p class=\"css-at9mc1 evys1bk0\">The two boxes and the other artifacts stolen in the heist have not been recovered &mdash; and it is not the first time that thieves have targeted the Mus&eacute;e Cognacq-Jay.</p>\r\n<p class=\"css-at9mc1 evys1bk0\">In March 1937,&nbsp;<a class=\"css-yywogo\" title=\"\" href=\"https://www.nytimes.com/1937/03/06/archives/paris-museum-robbed-eighteenth-century-jewels-are-taken-from-the.html\">The New York Times reported</a>&nbsp;that several 18th-century gold snuff boxes and items of jewelry had been taken by a gang who smashed their way into a glass display case.</p>\r\n<p class=\"css-at9mc1 evys1bk0\">On that occasion, the suspects were described as a &ldquo;blond young woman and an elderly woman, and a bewhiskered, decorated man.&rdquo;</p>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</section>', '', '/uploads/84c4610c-567e-4dde-97d2-bac567bc9d60_31cul-royals-theft-01-hwqv-jumbo.jpg', '2025-08-01', '2025-08-01 07:33:45', '2025-08-01 07:33:45'),
(32, 'The Changing Map of Palestinian Recognition', 'the-changing-map-of-palestinian-recognition', 'The Changing Map of Palestinian Recognition', '<header class=\"css-1qv3lay euiyums1\">\r\n<div class=\"css-1vkm6nb ehdk2mb0\">\r\n<h1 id=\"link-5a91a9a6\" class=\"css-88wicj e1h9rw200\" data-testid=\"headline\">The Changing Map of Palestinian Recognition</h1>\r\n</div>\r\n<p id=\"article-summary\" class=\"css-79rysd e1wiw3jv0\">In the past week alone, three new countries have said they are ready to bestow recognition on a Palestinian state.</p>\r\n<div class=\"css-qznc1j\">\r\n<div class=\"css-1e4xg23\">\r\n<div class=\"css-1von7hd\">\r\n<div class=\"css-b8gc4a\">\r\n<div class=\"css-79elbk\">&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div class=\"css-uepebd\">\r\n<div class=\"css-35ezg3\">Listen to this article&nbsp;&middot; 2:06 min&nbsp;<span class=\"css-14h5vr8\"><a href=\"https://help.nytimes.com/hc/en-us/articles/24318293692180\">Learn more</a></span></div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"css-1pec0v7\">\r\n<div class=\"css-yomkvi\" role=\"toolbar\" data-testid=\"share-tools\" aria-label=\"Social Media Share buttons, Save button, and Comments Panel with current comment count\">\r\n<div class=\"css-17cfcd4\">&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div class=\"css-ac2f9k\" data-testid=\"share-tools-menu\">\r\n<ul class=\"css-16g9egj\" data-testid=\"share-tools-list\">\r\n<li class=\"css-1obgmli\">\r\n<div class=\"css-vxcmzt\">&nbsp;</div>\r\n</li>\r\n<li class=\"css-19yhb3c save-button\">&nbsp;</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<section id=\"2025-07-30-palestinian-recognition-world\" class=\"interactive-content interactive-size-scoop css-1t58pk9\" data-testid=\"inline-interactive\" data-id=\"100000010314538\" data-source-id=\"100000010314538\">\r\n<div id=\"embed-id-100000010314538\" class=\"css-17ih8de interactive-body\" data-sourceid=\"100000010314538\">\r\n<div id=\"g-world-box\" class=\"ai2html ai2html-responsive ai2html-resizer\" role=\"img\">\r\n<div id=\"g-world-Artboard_31\" class=\"g-artboard\" data-aspect-ratio=\"1.915\" data-min-width=\"945\">\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<img id=\"g-world-Artboard_31-img\" class=\"g-world-Artboard_31-img g-aiImg\" src=\"https://static01.nytimes.com/newsgraphics/bk-OvZJjaPIAQofXw/EM2rgJihcjMaAUqRJ1kHsqiVt3Y/_assets/world-Artboard_31.png\" alt=\"\" data-src=\"https://static01.nytimes.com/newsgraphics/bk-OvZJjaPIAQofXw/EM2rgJihcjMaAUqRJ1kHsqiVt3Y/_assets/world-Artboard_31.png\">\r\n<div id=\"g-ai2-1\" class=\"g-text g-aiAbs g-aiPointText\"></div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<footer id=\"interactive-footer\" class=\"css-nt2azn interactive-footer\">\r\n<p id=\"interactive-credit\" class=\"css-cudxsp interactive-credit\" data-testid=\"credit\"></p>\r\n</footer></section>\r\n<div class=\"css-p6m5rf\">\r\n<div class=\"byline-container css-1u5onbp epjyd6m2\">\r\n<div class=\"css-165eim7 ey68jwv0\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><a class=\"css-uwwqev\" href=\"https://www.nytimes.com/by/ashley-wu\"><img class=\"css-dc6zx6 ey68jwv2\" title=\"Ashley Wu\" src=\"https://static01.nyt.com/images/2021/09/21/multimedia/author-ashley-wu/author-ashley-wu-thumbLarge-v2.png\" alt=\"Ashley Wu\"></a></div>\r\n<div class=\"css-233int epjyd6m1\">\r\n<p class=\"css-4anu6l e1jsehar1\"><span class=\"byline-prefix\">By&nbsp;</span><a class=\"last-byline css-ojhyzr e1jsehar0\" itemprop=\"name\" href=\"https://www.nytimes.com/by/ashley-wu\">Ashley Wu</a></p>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"css-1c72mta\"><time class=\"css-kx0gap e16638kd0\" datetime=\"2025-07-30T19:30:06-04:00\">July 30, 2025</time></div>\r\n<div class=\"css-1arl30t\"><a class=\"css-1yuai0v\" title=\"Read in Spanish\" href=\"https://www.nytimes.com/es/2025/07/31/espanol/mundo/palestina-reconocimiento-internacional.html\" data-version=\"es\">Leer en espa&ntilde;ol</a></div>\r\n</header>\r\n<div id=\"NYT_ABOVE_MAIN_CONTENT_REGION\" data-testid=\"region\">\r\n<div>\r\n<div>\r\n<div>\r\n<div class=\"\">\r\n<div class=\"css-1lpvp6o\">&nbsp;</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<section class=\"meteredContent css-ar1ez3\">\r\n<div class=\"css-1vkgw65\" data-testid=\"floating-button\">\r\n<div class=\"css-vxcmzt\">\r\n<div class=\"css-79elbk\">&nbsp;</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"css-s99gbd StoryBodyCompanionColumn\" data-testid=\"companionColumn-0\">\r\n<div class=\"css-53u6y8\">\r\n<p class=\"css-at9mc1 evys1bk0\">Most countries in the United Nations &mdash; 147 out of 193 &mdash; already recognize a Palestinian state, which currently has observer status at the U.N.</p>\r\n<p class=\"css-at9mc1 evys1bk0\">Then, in the course of just the past week, three more countries &mdash; all major U.S. allies &mdash; said they would join their ranks.</p>\r\n<p class=\"css-at9mc1 evys1bk0\">First,&nbsp;<a class=\"css-yywogo\" title=\"\" href=\"https://www.nytimes.com/2025/07/24/world/europe/france-palestine-statehood-macron-gaza.html\">France</a>&nbsp;said it would recognize a Palestinian state in September, and in the days that followed,&nbsp;<a class=\"css-yywogo\" title=\"\" href=\"https://www.nytimes.com/2025/07/29/world/europe/uk-palestine-state-starmer-gaza-israel.html\">Britain</a>&nbsp;and&nbsp;<a class=\"css-yywogo\" title=\"\" href=\"https://www.nytimes.com/2025/07/30/world/canada/canada-palestinian-state-recognition.html\">Canada</a>&nbsp;announced that they, too, were prepared to follow suit. Britain said it would move forward if Israel did not agree to a cease-fire with Hamas in Gaza by September, while Canada tied a final decision to political changes by the Palestinian Authority.</p>\r\n<p class=\"css-at9mc1 evys1bk0\">The announcements reflect the&nbsp;<a class=\"css-yywogo\" title=\"\" href=\"https://www.nytimes.com/2025/07/25/world/middleeast/macron-france-palestinian-statehood.html\">deep frustrations</a> with Israel&rsquo;s conduct of the war in Gaza, analysts say, which has killed tens of thousands of Palestinians and left a population of about two million in a state of extreme privation and hunger.</p>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</section>', '', '/uploads/cf2e1200-64c3-4608-b113-ad966e4cb081_europe-600.png', '2025-08-01', '2025-08-01 15:30:55', '2025-08-01 15:31:38');

